<title type="html"><![CDATA[3/28(Sat.) Top Instagram Updates in 2020/The achievements that matter most, and why]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=377&amp;p=394#p394"><![CDATA[
3/28(Sat.)<br />Top Instagram Updates in 2020/The achievements that matter most, and why（Host Michelle)<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://adespresso.com/blog/instagram-updates-you-need-to-make/">https://adespresso.com/blog/instagram-u ... d-to-make/</a><!-- m --><br /><br />It’s time for another month’s worth of Instagram updates! But it’s also a crazy time out there right now, and we hope that everyone is staying safe and heathy!<br /><br />1. Have you ever used Instagram?<br />2.What do you think the difference between Instagram and 3.another social media?<br />4.What do you think the best way to record your life？<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.cam.ac.uk/women-at-cambridge/chapters-and-themes/chapter-1-the-achievements-that-matter-most-and-why">https://www.cam.ac.uk/women-at-cambridg ... st-and-why</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Achievements are the building blocks that enable someone to construct a sense of themselves as a success. The achievements that matter most combine to form a version of success that has meaning and substance for the individual. Achievements also provide tangible evidence that colleagues, competitors and the wider world use to judge a person as more or less successful.<br /><br />1.Please share your experiences of achievement.<br />2.Please share what do you want to achieve and how.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=25764">Michelle Hsu</a> — Sat Mar 28, 2020 10:41 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
